lyrics:
[verse]
In this dim-lit room, troubles start to weigh me down
Sippin' on the same old drink, in this weary little town
I need a potion strong and true, to lift me from my sorrow
A new elixir, bold and sweet, to bring a brighter tomorrow

[chorus]
Pour me a new libation, a concoction strong and true
A drink to heal my weary soul, a remedy for what I'm going through
In this barroom of old worries, let a new spirit set me free
A potion to chase away the blues, to raise a glass to life's jubilee
